    "D. Putting Everything TogetherWe summarize the training strategy of the t-READi, and present the overall workflow as follows.",
    "With the strategy presented in §III-C, t-READi re-trains the model under missing modality settings, allowing each sensor to fail independently.",
    "During the following tuning phase, which addresses various scenarios with variation, t-READi is constrained by two parameters, namely rank bound k and projection squeeze ratio r, as we have discussed their insights in §III-B above.In reality, a cocktail of domain-specific variations muddles the situation, rendering the tuning of the entire domain space anything from unmanageable to impossible.",
    "Yet, by employing tuned parameters from individual variations, we squeeze the combined domain's tuning scope from M × N to a more manageable M + N (respecting lidar and camera modalities).",
    "Furthermore, we find unseen domains like nighttime often share traits with seen domains, such as underexposure."
